SCENE STRUCTURE GUIDANCE
=========================
Isolation scenes show the perpetrator systematically severing the victim's support network:
  1. Trigger — victim mentions a planned visit, call, or message to the isolation target.
  2. Criticism — perpetrator begins with mild criticism of the person (they're toxic, interfering).
  3. Reframing — frames the victim's relationship with the person as harmful or disloyal to the couple.
  4. Blame transfer — implies the victim prefers that person over their partner.
  5. Prohibition — forbids or strongly pressures victim to cancel the contact.
The perpetrator never explicitly says "I forbid you" early on — the control emerges gradually.

